"By leveraging our cash on hand to invest in bitcoin now, we have transformed our potential to be a pure-play investment into a reality," said Okamoto. "We also believe that holding part of our treasury reserves in bitcoin will be a better long-term strategy than holding U.S. dollars, similar to other forward-thinking companies like <a href="https://www.theblockcrypto.com/linked/92111/microstrategy-buys-additional-bitcoin-10-million-btc" data-v-f87c67ca="">MicroStrategy</a>."<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
To be sure, <a href="https://www.theblockcrypto.com/post/89771/crypto-stocks-soar-amid-bitcoin-rally" data-v-f87c67ca="">Marathon's stock rallied 892% last year </a>and MicroStrategy's stock gained 166%, as compared to bitcoin's gain of about 300% during the year.&nbsp;
